data.Name: Greeting
data.Description: Welcome children warmly. Give them your full attention. Have activities available for them to do

data.Name: Message board
data.Description: When all children have arrived, gather around the message board. Talk through each message, by pointing to the symbols. Involve the children.

data.Name: Small group
data.Description: Break into smaller groups. Show the whole group what to do and then go around helping individual children.

data.Name: Free play
data.Description: Plan-Play-Recall is an important life skill. It helps children to plan their time, and then review how the time was spent.
data.Alert: Build in toilet time, snack time, and outdoor play (if you have the space). Small and large group activities and free play can be indoors or outdoors.

data.Name: Large group
data.Description: This is a fun time for the whole group to do something together. Group games, acting out stories, making music, singing songs or dancing. It builds a feeling of togetherness.
